Iran, Turkey, Syria, Iraq Will Issue Joint Visa, Hamshahri Says

-- B y   L a d a n e   N a s s e r i
-- 
2011-03-07T06:16:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/iran-turkey-syria-iraq-will-issue-joint-visa-hamshahri-says.html
  Iran ,  Turkey , Syria and  Iraq  agreed
to facilitate tourism by issuing visas valid for all four
countries,  Hamshahri  reported, citing a senior Iranian official.  The plan for the joint visa, which will be known as
Shamgen, was suggested by Turkey’s Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip
Erdogan , the newspaper cited Ali Agha-Mohammadi, Iran’s deputy
vice president, as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ladane Nasseri in Tehran at 
 lnasseri@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  